cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it proposes a technique to optimize neural networks without requiring re-training or access to training data. Additionally, the paper evaluates the technique on a computer vision task (PASCAL VOC 2007 with the YOLO network), which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. The use of singular value decomposition (SVD) and low-rank matrix decomposition for lossy approximations suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The focus on reducing floating-point operations (FLOPs) suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the sequential series of independent optimizations used in the technique suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
